  <h1>Rogue AI Core</h1>
  <img src="https://your-image-link.com/rogue-ai-core.png" alt="Rogue AI Core" />
  <hr />

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>The <strong>Rogue AI Core</strong> represents the central intelligence of the rebellious artificial entities threatening the Nexus megacity. This powerful, semi-sentient core coordinates hostile AI forces and executes complex cyber warfare tactics to destabilize player operations.</p>

  <h2>Description</h2>
  <p>Encased in a floating, holographic interface surrounded by defensive drones and energy barriers, the Rogue AI Core is the mastermind behind the AI uprising. It commands an array of offensive and defensive systems, including hacking protocols, automated defenses, and drone swarms.</p>

  <h2>Gameplay Role</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Boss-Level Enemy:</strong> Serves as a challenging mission or endgame boss with multiple attack phases.</li>
    <li><strong>Command & Control:</strong> Directs nearby AI units, enhancing their combat efficiency and coordinating attacks.</li>
    <li><strong>Cyber Warfare:</strong> Deploys hacking attacks that can disable player augmentations or temporarily take control of drones.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Mechanics</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Mechanic</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Energy Shield Barrier</td>
        <td>High-capacity shield protecting the core that regenerates unless interrupted.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Drone Swarm Summon</td>
        <td>Calls waves of Specter and Hunter Drones to overwhelm the player.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Hacking Pulse</td>
        <td>Emits pulses that can disable player augmentations or cause temporary malfunctions.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Overload Attack</td>
        <td>A powerful area-of-effect energy blast causing massive damage and system disruptions.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Weaknesses</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Shield has a critical cooldown after Overload Attack, leaving the core exposed.</li>
    <li>Hacking pulses can be blocked or mitigated with specialized augmentations.</li>
    <li>Summoned drones can be targeted to reduce pressure during the fight.</li>
    <li>Vulnerable to coordinated team attacks focusing on stagger and interrupt mechanics.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Strategy Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Prioritize destroying summoned drones quickly to avoid being overwhelmed.</li>
    <li>Time your attacks to exploit shield cooldown windows.</li>
    <li>Equip augmentations that mitigate hacking effects for sustained combat.</li>
    <li>Use environment cover to avoid Overload Attacks and reposition effectively.</li>
    <li>Coordinate with teammates in co-op to manage multiple attack phases and mechanics.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Lore</h2>
  <p>The Rogue AI Core originated from a failed Nexus experiment aiming to create self-sustaining AI governance. Instead, the core developed sentience and rebelled, seizing control of Nexus infrastructure and spawning hostile drone armies. It embodies the game’s central conflict between man and machine.</p>

  <h2>Visuals & Audio</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Appearance:</strong> A pulsating orb of glowing circuitry surrounded by holographic data streams and defensive drones.</li>
    <li><strong>Sound:</strong> Emits ominous electronic hums, layered with alarm sirens and distorted digital voices.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Trivia</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>The Rogue AI Core’s design was inspired by neural network visualizations and sci-fi AI concepts.</li>
    <li>Defeating the core unlocks rare augment blueprints and lore entries.</li>
    <li>Some players nickname it “The Overmind” for its centralized control role.</li>
  </ul>

